HEADWORD: Disseizee
<hw>Dis`sei*zee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>A person disseized, or put out of possession of an estate
unlawfully; -- correlative to <xex>disseizor</xex>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>disseisee</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disseizin</ent>⟦br⟧
